            <arrangement id="aspace_cb5748799a18cd8ee378bf8643e2223e">
               <head>Arrangement</head>
               <p>Organized into three subseries: Writings by James Merrill, Writings of Others, and Other Papers. Writings by James Merrill are arranged alphabetically by title, with untitled writings filed at the end of the subseries. Writings of Others are arranged alphabetically by author.</p>
            </arrangement>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_9a51be58042c498cc0fdd9dff0cefaf8">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Writings by James Merrill contain mostly typescript drafts of Merrill's writings, many containing manuscript corrections and notes. Also included are proofs, notebooks, and correspondence related to Merrill's works. Writings of Others include the libretto of <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                     <part>Phaedra: An Opera in Two Acts</part>
                  </title>, by Bernard de Zogheb, which contains a foreword written by Merrill; as well as photocopies of a poetic tribute to James Merrill, written by Rachel Hadas. Other Papers include a photograph of Merrill and a plate engraved with a swan.</p>
            </scopecontent>
